dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v1.factory

Class TresosDBFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v1.factory.TresosDBFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITresosDBFactory, IVerifyTresosDBFactory

    public class TresosDBFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements ITresosDBFactory, IVerifyTresosDBFactory
    This factory is used to create classes for the tresosDB interfaces found in dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v1.factory. The factory provides a reflective interface for creating instances: 
      IAUTOSAR autosar = TresosDBFactory.getInstance().create( IAUTOSAR.class );
  IEcuSwComposition comp = TresosDBFactory.getInstance().create( IEcuSwComposition.class, "MyComposition" );
    or the more type save variant with type specific methods: 
      IAUTOSAR autosar = TresosDBFactory.getInstance().createAUTOSAR();
  IEcuSwComposition comp = TresosDBFactory.getInstance().createEcuSwComposition( "MyComposition" );

        public IEndToEndProtectionISignalIPdu createEndToEndProtectionISignalIPdu()
        Create an instance of IEndToEndProtectionISignalIPdu.

        It is possible to protect the inter-ECU data exchange of safety-related ISignal (refering to a SystemSignalGroup) at the level of COM IPdus using protection mechanisms provided by E2E Library. For each ISignal to be protected, a separate E2EProtectionISignalIPdu element must be created within the EndToEndProtectionSet. The E2EProtectionISignalIPdu element refers to the ISignal that is to be protected and to the ISignalIPdu that transmits the protected ISignal. The information how the referenced ISignal shall be protected (through which E2E Profile and with which E2E settings) is defined in the EndToEndDescription element.

        Returns:
        the new instance (never null)
